**APPROACH 1     O(n) & O(1)**

* **ALGORITHM**
* **Iterating the string from beginning.**
	* **take a cnt variable**, and **increase the cnt when you find an open parenthesis '('.**
	* when you **find a close parenthiesis**, **2 cases were checked.**
	* i**f cnt is 0** , that **means no open parenthesis has occured earlier**.
	* therefore **replace the string index with '#'.**
	* **otherwise decrease the cnt**, as a **valid pair has found**.

* Now **iterate the string from behind** and **repeat the same steps** , but **this time check for closing parenthisis**.
	* if **closing parenthesis occur increase the cnt**.
	* if **open parenthesis occur**, now **again 2 cases are need to check.**
	* if the **cnt == 0, that means no closing parenthisis occur** before **therfore replace that string index with '#'.**
	* Otherwise **decrease the cnt.**
* **At end make the resultant string by excluding '#'**
* **Time Complexity** is O(n+n+n) = **O(n)**  for each 3 steps
* **Space Complexity** is **O(1)** , No extra space taken excluding result string.
```
```

**CODE WITH EXPLANATION**
```
					// 😉😉😉😉Please upvote if it helps 😉😉😉😉
class Solution
{
public:
    string minRemoveToMakeValid(string s)
    {
        int n = s.length();
        string res = "";

        int cnt = 0;
        // iterating from beginnning
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); ++i)
        {
            // if we find and open parenthesis increase the cnt
            if (s[i] == '(')
                ++cnt;
            // if we found an close parenthisis
            // check if cnt == 0 , that means we have no earlier open parenthesis,
            // therefore replace that index by '#'
            else if (s[i] == ')')
            {
                if (cnt == 0)
                    s[i] = '#';
                // else decrease the cnt beacuse a valid pair is found
                else
                    --cnt;
            }
        }

        cnt = 0;
        // iterating from the end
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; --i)
        {
            // if we find and close parenthesis increase the cnt
            if (s[i] == ')')
                ++cnt;
            // if we found an open parenthisis
            // check if cnt == 0 , that means we have no earlier close parenthesis,
            // therefore replace that index by '#'
            else if (s[i] == '(')
            {
                if (cnt == 0)
                    s[i] = '#';
                // else decrease the cnt beacuse a valid pair is found
                else
                    --cnt;
            }
        }

        // making the resultant string by excluding '#'
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); ++i)
        {
            if (s[i] != '#')
                res.push_back(s[i]);
        }

        return res;
    }
};
```

**APPROACH 2 USING STACK**

* **ALGORITHM**
``` ```
* **Using Stack** for **checking valadity of parenthesis**.
* first it**erate the string** and when you **find a open parenthesis push it into the stack**.
* if You **find and close parenthesis** , then **check if the stack is not empty**, if **stack is not empt**y that m**eans open parenthesis exist** **therefore pop the open parenthesis from the stack.**
* **if the stack is empty** that **means no open parenthesis exist first** therefore **replace that string index with '#'.**
* Now  there **may be a  case that string contain only open parenthesis** that is also an **invalid parenthesis.**
* therefore **while stack doesn't become empty** **marked the indexes from the stack top with '#'.**
* **pop that parenthesis from the stack.**
* Now **at end** **create the resultant string excluding '#'**
* **Time Complexity** is = **O(n)** 
* **Space Complexity** is **O(n)** , stack used.
```
```

**CODE WITH EXPLANATION**

```
						// 😉😉😉😉Please upvote if it helps 😉😉😉😉
class Solution
{
public:
    string minRemoveToMakeValid(string s)
    {
        stack<int> st;
        string res = "";

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); ++i)
        {
            // if we find open parenthesis push it to stack
            if (s[i] == '(')
                st.push(i);
            // if we find close parenthisis check
            // if there is a open parenthisis or the stack is empty
            else if (s[i] == ')')
            {
                // if stack  is empty then we need to remove that index from string
                // replacing it with '#' for our convenience
                if (st.empty())
                    s[i] = '#';
                else
                    // if there is an open parenthesis than remove that  from the stack
                    st.pop();
            }
        }

        // now , if stack is not empty that means it has open parenthesis
        // which have no closing parenthesis.
        // so we have to replace that index of string with '#' for our convenience
        while (!st.empty())
        {
            s[st.top()] = '#';
            st.pop();
        }

        // making the resultant string by excluding '#'
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); ++i)
        {
            if (s[i] != '#')
                res.push_back(s[i]);
        }

        return res;
    }
};
```

