solutions.content:
Perform a linear scan of the input string `s` and use a stack `S` to store each the index of each `'('` character.  Whenever a `')'` character is seen, pop the index of the nearest corresponding match (if possible), otherwise if the stack is empty, then mark the current index to be deleted, ie. we add the index onto the set `X`.  Upon completion of the linear scan, we append "leftover" indices of the stack `S` onto `X` to be deleted.

In summary:

1. we mark indices of `')'` to be deleted **during** the linear scan of the input string `s`
2. we mark indices of `'('` to be deleted **after** the linear scan of the input string `s`

---

*Kotlin*
```
class Solution {
    fun minRemoveToMakeValid(s: String): String {
        var X = mutableSetOf<Int>()
        var S = mutableListOf<Int>()
        for ((i, c) in s.toCharArray().withIndex()) {
            if (c == '(')
                S.add(i)
            if (c == ')') {
                if (0 < S.size)
                    S.removeAt(S.lastIndex)
                else
                    X.add(i)
            }
        }
        for (i in S) X.add(i)
        return s.toCharArray().withIndex().filter{ (i, c) -> !X.contains(i) }.map{ (_, c) -> c }.joinToString("")
    }
}
```

*Javascript*
```
let minRemoveToMakeValid = (s, S = [], X = new Set()) => {
    for (let i = 0; i < s.length; ++i) {
        let c = s[i];
        if (c == '(')
            S.push(i);
        if (c == ')') {
            if (S.length)
                S.pop();
            else
                X.add(i);
        }
    }
    S.forEach(i => X.add(i));
    return s.split('').filter((_, i) => !X.has(i)).join('');
};
```

