# Intuition
Just guessing which bracket is wrongly placed makes the problem more difficult as it can be anywhere.

So basic intuition could be, finding the wrong bracket's or we can say unwanted bracket's indices in the string.

# Approach
Approach is very similar to that of finding valid parenthesis.

Suppose we have ( ( ) ( ( ) ) ) ) ) (.

Now lets try to find valid parenthesis using stack : - 
- ( - pushed , idx = 0
- ( - pushed , idx = 1
- ) - valid match as top of stack '(' ,so popped last '(', idx = 2

we can continue this way and at the end we would be having only unwanded bracket.


If you find a pair, that is valid one else it is invalid.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
    O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string minRemoveToMakeValid(string s) {

        stack<pair<char,int>> st;

        for(int i = 0 ; i  < s.length() ; i++){
            if(s[i]=='('){
                st.push({s[i],i});
            }else if(s[i]==')'){
                if(!st.empty() && st.top().first=='(')st.pop();
                else st.push({s[i],i});
            }
        }

        string str = "";

        for(int i = s.length()-1; i>=0 ; i--){
            if(!st.empty() && st.top().second == i){
                st.pop();
                continue;
            }else str+=s[i];

        }

        reverse(str.begin(),str.end());
        return str;
    }
};
```

