solutions.content:
So, the problem of the valid parentheses is a classic declined in several variations - like this one that has filler characters - nothing too complex, but still a minor hindrance to consider.

To solve this problem, we will first of all declare a few support variables:
* `tmp` is an array of chars, with the same size of `s`;
* `p` will count how many parentheses we opened, while `pos` will be the pointer we will use to work on `tmp` - both will be set to `0`.

In our first pass through all the characters in the input string, we will have 3 base case:
* `c == '('` will make it add to `tmp` (and increase `pos`), on top of increasing the dedicated `p` counter;
* `c == ')'` will add the character to `tmp` only if `p > 0` and we will do nothing otherwise (ie: the character is ignored);
* we will add any other character to `tmp`.

Once done, we will have stored `pos` character to compose a new, filtered string; but we might also have potentially `p` open parentheses that need to be removed.

To do so, we will generate out result variable `res` to be `pos - p` characters long and then proceed to fill it from the right, always adding each character that is not an opened parentheses, decreasing `p` otherwise and actually adding `'('` only after `p` is `<= 0` - meaning we got rid of the extra `p` open parentheses we collected before (whereas we can be sure that `tmp` will never have any extra closed parentheses).

Once done, we can return `res` :)

The code:

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    string minRemoveToMakeValid(string s) {
        // support variables
        char tmp[s.size()];
        int p = 0, pos = 0;
        for (char c: s) {
            switch(c) {
                case '(':
                    p++;
                    tmp[pos++] = c;
                    break;
                case ')':
                    // inserting closing parentheses only with p > 0
                    if (p > 0) {
                        p--;
                    }
                    else break;
                default:
                    tmp[pos++] = c;
            }
        }
        // properly sizing res
        string res(pos - p, '*');
        for (int i = pos - 1, j = pos - p - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (tmp[i] != '(' || p-- <= 0) res[j--] = tmp[i];
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

