# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The idea is to fill up the extra brackets with garbage character using two different loops. 
- The first loop fills up the extra ```)``` with ```$```. To fill up the ```)``` we need to hover from first to last to catch the extra ones. 
- The second loop fulls up the extra ```(``` with ```$```. To fill up the ```(``` we need to hover from last to first to catch the extra ones.
- Then loop through the updated string and discard the ```$``` character. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity: **O(n)**
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: **O(1)**
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string minRemoveToMakeValid(string s) {
        int brackets=0,n=s.length();
        string res;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(s[i]=='(') brackets++;
            else if(s[i]==')'){
                if(brackets==0)s[i]='$';
                else brackets--;
            }
        }
        brackets=0;
        for(int i=n-1;i>=0;i--){
            if(s[i]==')')brackets++;
            else if(s[i]=='('){
                if(brackets==0) s[i]='$';
                else brackets--;
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++)
            if(s[i]!='$')res+=s[i];
        return res;
    }
};
```

