// 2- This can be done using stack pair (pair<char,int>) which will contain parenthesis and its index.
// 3- Simple idea is that if we are hitting any close parenthesis then check for open parenthesis on top of the stack, if it is present simply pop out, otherwise insert the current parenthesis with index into the stack.
// 4- traverse into the stack and remove all parenthesis from string having index equal to index into stack.
class Solution {
public:
    string minRemoveToMakeValid(string s) {
        stack<pair<char,int>>st;
        int n=s.size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(s[i]=='(')
                st.push({s[i],i});
