*********************************************Explanations************************************
-->In the given que we need to remove the extra '(' & ')' (brackets).
-->first apporach in my mind that we use string , stack , map  and so on.
-->so , I m using the string .
-->firstly  iterate the loop from the starting and the secondly iterate the loop from the ending.
--> so , my apporach is that we iterate the loop from the starting  and if we find the "("(opening bracket) , then increment it , and if we find the ")"(closing bracket) is more then the "(" then we need to decrement it .(no. closing> no.opening)
--> thats why we are using the s[i]=='@', and decrement the count --;
--> second loop started from the end  . 
--> if no. opening > the no. closing  , then decrement the '(' (opening)
--> at last run the  loop 

