solutions.content:
**1249. Minimum Remove to Make Valid Parentheses**

##### **APPROACH -**
* **Each prefix of a balanced parentheses has a number of open parentheses greater or equal than closed parentheses, similar idea with each suffix.**

*Create **`count`** to keep track of the net number of parentheses
Iterate from left to right to check for invalid **`')'`**
While maintaining the count, mark the invalid ones with **`'*'`**
Reset count and again iterate from right to left to check for invalid **`'('`**
While maintaining the count, mark the invalid ones with **`'*'`**
Now get the result removing all the invalid **`'*'`** we marked*

**Note : Removing only the invalid parentheses ensures the minimum condition given in the problem statement**

<br/>

##### **COMPLEXITY -**
* **Time Complexity : O(N)**, where N = length of s
* **Space Complexity : O(1)**

<br/>

##### **CODE -**
```
class Solution {
public:
    string minRemoveToMakeValid(string s) {
        int count = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < s.length(); ++i) {
            if(s[i] == '(')    ++count;
            else if(s[i] == ')') {
                if(count > 0)   --count;
                else   s[i] = '*';  // invalid as number of '(' on left is less than the number of ')'
            }
        }

        count = 0;
        for(int i = s.length()-1; i >= 0 ; --i) {
            if(s[i] == ')')    ++count;
            else if(s[i] == '(') {
                if(count > 0)   --count;
                else   s[i] = '*';  // invalid as number of ')' on right is less than the number of '('
            }
        }

        string res;
        for(char c : s) {
            if(c != '*')    
                res.push_back(c);
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

