solutions.content:
Task :- 
1. Remove minimum no. of brackets to make a valid string(i.e take as many brackets as possible in our string).

Observations :-
1. for every opening bracket a closing bracket should be present in a valid string.

Steps :-
1. iterate over the string if the current character is not a bracket simply add this to our ans.
2. if it is an opening bracket we can simply check that whether a closing bracket is present for this opening bracket or not present.
3. if it is present we can add this opening bracket into our ans and we can mark that we have used this closing bracket for an opening bracket and now we can't use this closing bracket for any other opening bracket.
4.  if its a closing bracket we can check that whether we have used this closing bracket for an opening bracket or not if yes we have to add this in our ans otherwise not.

Code :-

```
public String minRemoveToMakeValid(String s) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();

        boolean[] taken = new boolean[s.length()];

        for(int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            char ch = s.charAt(i);

            if(ch != '(' && ch != ')') {  // if the current character is not a bracket
                sb.append(ch);
            } else if(ch == '(') {  // if it is an opening bracket find the nearest closing bracket and mark it taken
                int j = i + 1;
                while(j < s.length() && (s.charAt(j) != ')' || (taken[j] == true))) {
                    j++;
                }

                if(j < s.length()) {
                    taken[j] = true;
                    sb.append(ch);
                }
            } else { // if it is a closing bracket and we have used it for some opening bracket then add it into our ans
                if(taken[i] == true) {
                    sb.append(ch);
                }
            }
        }

        return sb.toString();
    }
```

Time Complexity :- O(n^2)

