The idea is to use a stack to store indexes of invalid parentheses, because we need to remove those parentheses to make the string valid.
Idea is same as:
https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-valid-parentheses/discuss/525900/JAVA-simple-stack-solution-O(n)-with-explanation
https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-add-to-make-parentheses-valid/discuss/525953/JAVA-one-pass-stack-solution-with-explanation

```
    public String minRemoveToMakeValid(String s) {
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            char c = s.charAt(i);
            if (c == '(') {
                stack.push(i);
            } else if (c == ')') {
                if (!stack.isEmpty() && s.charAt(stack.peek()) == '(') {
                    stack.pop();
                } else {
                    stack.push(i);
                }
            }
        }
        Set<Integer> invalidIndexes = new HashSet<>(stack);
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            if (invalidIndexes.contains(i)) continue;
            sb.append(s.charAt(i));
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
