Hey Everyone!
Here we will follow simple and easy approach....
By looking at the Problem Statement , we came to know that we want to remove unwanted parentheses from the String and return the new String.
We will use StringBuilder to Store what we want in String (i.e removing unwanted parentheses)
so for that 
we have to first Traverse the String and check
**if char c is equal to '('**
then we will increment open by 1.
here open is the variable which will look on counting of parentheses '(' and ')'
by doing simple check is my  number of opening parentheses is equal to my closing parentheses or not 
if in case its more than required we will simply remove it.
But we also have to check before getting closing one there must be one opening one too
```
class Solution {
    public String minRemoveToMakeValid(String s) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        int open = 0;
        for(char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if(c =='(') {
                open++;

            }
            else if(c == ')') {
                if(open == 0) continue;
                open--;
            }
            sb.append(c);
        }

        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();
        for(int i=sb.length()-1 ; i>=0 ; i-- ){
            if(sb.charAt(i) == '(' && open-- > 0) continue;
            result.append(sb.charAt(i));


        }
        return result.reverse().toString(); 

        }

    }
