solutions.content:
Task -> We have to remove minimum number of parathesis, so that our string becomes valid. 

Solution -> 
There can be some observations, that we should observe.
1) if at any point count of closing paranthesis ')' is greater than opening paranthesis '(', then we have to remove closing paranthesis at that point only, because we can not validade a closing paranthesis by moving right,
2) but we can validate a opening paranthesis by moving right, because there can be same number of closing paranthesis in the right.
3) at last if we have count of opening paranthesis greater than closing, so we have to remove some opening paranthesis, 
4) so which paranthesis should be removed -----> the answer is pretty simple, remove the paranthesis from the right side of string, because we know if there are any closing paranthesis to right of these opening paranthesis that we are going to remove, these closing paranthesis can be validated by opening ones at left,
5) But if we start removing from left or start of string, there can be some closing paranthesis , that can not be validated by opening paranthesis in right of string.


Coding Part -> 
1) use cnt variable for counting of opening and closing paranthesis.
2) If we encounter opening paranthesis, then increment cnt.
3) If any closing paranthesis comes, decrement cnt.
4) If at any point cnt is negative, then remove that character. (that is closing paranthesis [see point 1 of observations]).
5) and at last after iterating , cnt is positive, then remove same amount of opening paranthesis from the end of string.
6) I removed paranthesis by updating that char with '#', you can pick any other character and after all operations, created a new string which will not contain '#' character.

See below code for more clearity.

`IF YOU LIKE MY EXPLANATION & CODE PLEASE DO UPVOTE (<>)`

```
class Solution {
public:
    string minRemoveToMakeValid(string s) {

        int cnt = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {

            if(s[i] == '(') cnt++;
            if(s[i] == ')') cnt--;
            if(cnt < 0) {

                s[i] = '#';
                cnt = 0;
            }
        }
        int idx = s.length() - 1;
        while(cnt > 0 && idx >= 0) {

            if(s[idx] == '(') {

                s[idx] = '#';
                cnt--;
            }
            idx--;
        }
        string res = "";
        for(char c : s) {

            if(c != '#') res += c;
        }

        return res;
    }
};
```

