# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We are given that they will play optimally, now think how would they play optimally? If you were at that place then you would definitely want max advantage to yourself and maximum loss to the other one so just sum the value of alice and bob which are at same index and select the one with the maximum sum in this way we can play optimally but now we want maximum sum in minimum time...we can think of max heap as it give us maximmum element in O(1) TC 

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Create a max heap to store the sum of aliceValues and bobValues and the index i , in my case I have used class mine to store them
2. I have created variables alice and bob to store their store and an additional boolean variable to track the turn of players
3. Now we will process items till the max heap does not become empty (Using While loop)
4. In loop,Take out the top element of heap and pop it
5. Take out the Index from it
6. see whose turn it is 
7. if alice turn , take value from aliceValues and add it to alice score...do same for bob
8. Return as per given in question

